modules.description: This module defines a data structure for representing raw configuration parameters parsed from a file, supporting operations to parse strings into typed values and serialize them to an output channel. It works with a custom variant type `cp` that captures primitive and compound configuration values like strings, integers, lists, and nested sections. It is used to load and print configuration data directly, without intermediate type wrapping.

This module processes configuration files with key-value pairs, supporting typed values like integers, floats, strings, booleans, lists, options, and enumerations. It provides classes and wrappers to define, parse, and manage configuration parameters with structured access, default values, and command-line integration. Use cases include loading application settings from files, generating formatted output, and synchronizing configuration state across different parts of a system.
